<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 08 at 8:09AM CDT until June 08 at 8:45AM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 845 AM CDT
FOR COLLINGSWORTH AND DONLEY COUNTIES...
At 808 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located over mainly rural
areas of Donley and Collingsworth counties, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wellington, Clarendon, Howardwick, Hedley, Dodson, Lutie, Lelia Lake,
Dozier, Samnorwood, Quail and Greenbelt Lake.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
